Sentencas: In this study, high-resolution focused ion beam sectioning assisted with SEM imaging was used to study the indentation microstructures of porous bulks and films of a solid oxide fuel cell cathode material (La0.6Sr0.4C0.2Fe0.8O3-delta) sintered at different temperatures.
Titulo: Characterisation of indentation microstructures for porous SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: The crack morphologies and pore-filling densification caused by crushing of particle networks were studied in details.
Titulo: Characterisation of indentation microstructures for porous SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: Analysis showed distinct permanent deformation mechanisms of the indentation microstructures between porous bulks and films.
Titulo: Characterisation of indentation microstructures for porous SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: Whilst remarkable porosity gradient was found for the porous films under both Berkovich and spherical indenters, the porous bulks were found to behave more like dense materials.
Titulo: Characterisation of indentation microstructures for porous SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: Results also showed that radial cracks induced by Berkovich indentation on the bulks could not generate observable pop-in/pop-out events in the loading-unloading curves.
Titulo: Characterisation of indentation microstructures for porous SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: However, when indenting with the spherical indenter on a thick film, the shear sliding of the particle networks immediately under the indenter could cause phenomenal disruption in the loading unloading curves shown.
Titulo: Characterisation of indentation microstructures for porous SOFC cathodes
